---
export const prerender = true;
import Gryphline from "../layouts/Gryphline.astro";
---
<Gryphline title="process">
  <section class="gl-shell">
    <p class="gl-kicker">case study · graphic design</p>
    <h1 class="gl-h1">the process<em>.</em></h1>
    <p class="gl-lede">
      Tokyo Zero is a small-drop anime merch project — 47 products, three thematic
      storefronts, one voice. Here's how the brand system, typography, and page
      architecture came together.
    </p>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">01 · voice + audience</h2>
      <p class="para">
        The core reader is the person who already knows the reference — Panty &amp; Stocking with
        Garterbelt, Needy Streamer Overload, Genshin, HoYo, Vtubers. The brand assumes fluency
        instead of explaining. Copy is short, lowercase, punchy — closer to a Discord message
        than a marketing brochure.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="pull">
        "small drops. heavy print. character work for the people who already know."
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">02 · three storefronts, one system</h2>
      <div class="tri">
        <div class="tri__cell">
          <p class="tri__label">misc</p>
          <h3 class="tri__title">catalog, curated</h3>
          <p>Magazine-style catalog with numbered cards, hairline dividers, slate-violet accent. The neutral hub between themed rooms.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tri__cell">
          <p class="tri__label">psg</p>
          <h3 class="tri__title">candy-halftone spectacle</h3>
          <p>Panty &amp; Stocking pastiche — hot pink frills, halftone circles, 7-card product showcase on a tilted cyan slab.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tri__cell">
          <p class="tri__label">nso</p>
          <h3 class="tri__title">crt streamer decay</h3>
          <p>Needy Streamer Overload homage — chrome bg, RGB-glitching popups, scanlines. Ame + KAngel sprites in the hero.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">03 · typography</h2>
      <div class="type-grid">
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Apex Mk3</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: var(--gl-mono);">.contact</p>
          <p class="face__role">Monospace. Titles, labels, navigation. Reads as terminal output — matches the "design + code" story.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Beam Visionary</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-style: italic;">from the desk.</p>
          <p class="face__role">Script. Eyebrows, brand marks. The one moment of handwriting in an otherwise-mechanical system.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Branding Pro</p>
          <p class="face__sample">Body copy, running text, product descriptions.</p>
          <p class="face__role">Sans. Body copy. Neutral, wide x-height, five weights. Does the invisible work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">NSO CRT</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: var(--gl-mono); letter-spacing: 0.06em;">SIGNAL &gt; NO SYNC</p>
          <p class="face__role">Pixel bitmap. NSO theme only. Chyrons, popup labels, HUD text. Ties the CRT visual metaphor together.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">04 · color</h2>
      <p class="para">
        Base palette locks the catalog in a soft-white / slate-violet universe. Each themed room
        breaks that mold — PSG goes hot pink + cyan + gold, NSO goes chrome + magenta + electric
        blue. The themes are supposed to feel like different shops; misc is the hallway between.
      </p>
      <div class="swatches">
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #f5f4f0"></span>#f5f4f0 · misc base</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #5061b9"></span>#5061b9 · slate violet</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #ff4da6"></span>#ff4da6 · psg pink</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #3deaff"></span>#3deaff · psg cyan</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #fd7ac0"></span>#fd7ac0 · nso magenta</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #ffb84d"></span>#ffb84d · nso amber</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-section">
      <h2 class="gl-h2">05 · character work</h2>
      <p class="para">
        Every product carries a hand-illustrated character. Deskmats print at 900×400mm with
        rounded corners; tapestries at 60×90cm on polyester with grommets; prints at 12×18in
        on satin card stock. The full character roster spans Genshin, Star Rail, HoYo IPs,
        Vtuber + Hololive members, and the two flagship PSG/NSO castings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="gl-panel gl-panel--elev cta">
      <span class="gl-panel__corner gl-panel__corner--tl"></span>
      <span class="gl-panel__corner gl-panel__corner--bl"></span>
      <span class="gl-panel__corner gl-panel__corner--br"></span>
      <p class="gl-kicker">next</p>
      <h2 class="gl-h2 cta__h">how it ships &rarr;</h2>
      <p class="gl-lede" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
        The whole storefront runs on a serverless AWS stack provisioned with Terraform.
        Walk through the infrastructure or browse the catalog.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 14px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a class="gl-btn gl-btn--primary" href="/architecture/">architecture <span class="gl-btn__arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="gl-btn" href="/catalog/">catalog <span class="gl-btn__arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .para {
      font-family: var(--gl-sans);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--gl-ink-soft);
      margin: 0 0 16px;
      max-width: 720px;
    }
    .pull {
      margin: 24px 0 0;
      padding: 20px 24px;
      background: var(--gl-cyan-soft);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--gl-cyan);
      font-family: var(--gl-display);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.4;
      color: var(--gl-ink);
    }
    .tri { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; margin-top: 24px; }
    .tri__cell {
      padding: 22px;
      background: var(--gl-bg-panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--gl-line);
      clip-path: polygon(0 0, calc(100% - 12px) 0, 100% 12px, 100% 100%, 0 100%);
    }
    .tri__label {
      font-family: var(--gl-mono);
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gl-cyan);
      margin: 0 0 10px;
    }
    .tri__title {
      font-family: var(--gl-display);
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      color: var(--gl-ink);
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }
    .tri p { font-family: var(--gl-sans); font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--gl-ink-soft); margin: 0; line-height: 1.5; }

    .type-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 24px; }
    .face {
      padding: 20px;
      background: var(--gl-bg-panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--gl-line);
      clip-path: polygon(0 0, calc(100% - 10px) 0, 100% 10px, 100% 100%, 0 100%);
    }
    .face__name {
      font-family: var(--gl-mono);
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gl-cyan);
      margin: 0 0 10px;
    }
    .face__sample {
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      margin: 4px 0 14px;
      line-height: 1.1;
      color: var(--gl-ink);
    }
    .face__role { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--gl-ink-soft); margin: 0; }

    .swatches { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; margin-top: 20px; }
    .sw { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; font-family: var(--gl-mono); font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--gl-ink-soft); }
    .sw span { display: inline-block; width: 28px; height: 28px; border: 1px solid var(--gl-line-strong); }

    .cta { margin-top: 6vh; }
    .cta__h { margin-bottom: 16px; }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .tri, .type-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</Gryphline>
